text.1: Every year over 1.3M people die on roads – the equivalent of a #COVID19 pandemic every single year. These aren't just numbers – they’re mothers, fathers, sisters, brothers, daughters & sons. Each year, around 1.35 million people die each year as a result of road traffic crashes globally.

Road traffic injuries and deaths are preventable.

Its #WorldDayofRememberance of road traffic victims. Today, we call on all to:
•Remember those who lost their lives on the roads 
•Support those who are bereaved & those who suffer the long-lasting consequences from the trauma
•Act to prevent such tragedies today & in future https://t.co/3sLY1mwKX0
